      <h1 class='title'>Meaning of "financial provision" and of references to specified financial provision</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='grand-committee-report-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HL Deb 17 May 2004 vol 661 c299GC</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_299gc' title='Col. 299GC &mdash; HL Deb 17 May 2004 vol 661 c299GC' name='column_299gc' href='#column_299gc' rel='bookmark'>299GC</a>
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-03873'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040517_GCR_484' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        10 (1) In this Part "financial provision" means any one or more of the following&#x2014;
        <ol>
        <li>(a) the making of periodical payments by one civil partner to the other;</li>
        <li>(b) the payment of a lump sum by one civil partner to the other;</li>
        <li>(c) the making of periodical payments by one civil partner to a child of the family or to the other civil partner for the benefit of such a child;</li>
        <li>(d) the payment by one party of a lump sum to a child of the family or to the other civil partner for the benefit of such a child.</li></ol>
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-03874'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040517_GCR_485' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        (2) Any reference in this Part to the financial provision specified in an application under this Part or a request under paragraph 14 or specified by the court is a reference&#x2014;
        <ol>
        <li>(a) to the type of provision specified in the application or request or by the court,</li>
        <li>(b) to the amount so specified as the amount of any payment to be made under the application or order, and</li>
        <li>(c) in the case of periodical payments, to the term so specified as the term for which the payments are to be made.</li></ol>
      </p>
      <ol class='xoxo'>
        
